author: Jenn Lacock

comment:
There is A LOT of misinformation in this video. Before anything, I want to say that AH is diabolical as a human being and I want nothing else but to see her go down. However:

1. Lawyers say 'allegations.' If Johnny hasn't been found guilty of anything, it's allegations. 

2. There is lawyer-client privilege. Howeveeerrrrrrr, if your client tells you something, even if it ruins your case, you have to bring it up. Sometimes lawyers, as a tactic, will bring up the information that ruins their case before the other side to get it out of the way. 
Also, this is why alot of lawyers will tell their clients to ONLY answer the questions they ask them. Lawyers don't want to hear everything, for literally this reason.

3. No they won't throw anything out if there's an error. This isn't a cops legal charging papers. It's a memorandum. They'll state that it's wrong and move on.
